  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> drained chickpeas </strong>to a baking tray with your <strong>ground coriander</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crispy – these are your <strong>crispy chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1593428821494-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1593428821494-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1593428821494-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1593428821494-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1593428821494-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed and chop finely</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ginger </strong>and<strong> coriander</strong> with your <strong>rice vinegar, </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>chilli dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1593428829393-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1593428829393-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
